{
  "texts": [
    "We find that the infidelities are commensurate in these two experiments.",
    "Using dynamic circuits with feedforward operations, we encode a two-qubit error-suppressed input magic state with a logical infidelity (1.87 ± 0.16) × 10 -2.",
    "In the post-selection experiment, we obtain an infidelity of (1.23 ± 0.11) × 10 -2.",
    "The feedforward operations in our experiment can introduce idling periods, of the order of hundreds of nanoseconds, during which additional errors can accumulate.",
    "To leading order we attribute the difference in fidelity between these preparation schemes to errors that occur while the control system is occupied performing the dynamical feedforward operation."
  ]
}